Plains Reopens Nipisi-Edmonton Portion of Rainbow Pipeline

-- B y   L y n n   D o a n
-- 
2011-05-25T22:59:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/plains-reopens-nipisi-edmonton-portion-of-rainbow-pipeline-1-.html
Plains Midstream  Canada  reopened the
24-inch Rainbow pipeline from Nipisi to Edmonton, the company
said on  its website .  The Calgary-based company said it restarted the crude line,
shut May 15 after wildfires cut power to it, at about 1 p.m.
local time.  The 20-inch Rainbow pipeline from Zama Lake to Nipisi
remains closed, pending restart approval by government
regulators. Plains said full-scale operations resumed at the
cleanup site today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lynn Doan in San Francisco at 
 ldoan6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Richard Stubbe at 
 rstubbe1@bloomberg.net  